Materials can be found on our OSF page: 
https://osf.io/pcu9g/?view_only=fce64a0be68e40b28f799ddf0a77b26a  
 
Participants will be measured once in a repeated measures (within-subject) design. They 
will be given a short demographic survey consisting of year of birth, gender, and US 
state in which they reside. They will then receive two short scales - the Coping Humor 
Scale, and the Life Orientation Test Revised. Last, they will rate 216 images, which are 
divided into COVID-meme, COVID-strip, COVID-text, and Non-COVID-text. Each 
participant will rate how funny they find the comic, and how disturbing they find the 
comic. The Coping Humor Scale and Life Orientation Test are not part of the focal 
hypotheses but are included to match the original study. We dropped a question about 
perceived risk of being infected by COVID-19, as it was unclear how to replicate the 
spatial analysis part of the study (if desired). The images have been classified into the 
same categories as the original study, however, these deviate from the originals as they 
are 1) in English, and 2) include many more than the original study due to power 
