The type of picture shown to the participant is manipulated and repeated within subjects. 
The pictures are the main analysis comparison, focusing on the comparison between the 

 
two verbal categories. These were selected by searching for “funny covid 
tweets/memes/comics” and selected from viral sites like Facebook, Buzzfeed, and other 
internet list articles of viral memes/tweets for each category. The original study only 
included 36 pictures (in Italian for text) and given the large size required for replication 
and power, we matched to the classification types used in the study:: 
1) COVID-meme: Primarily pictures focusing on COVID related themes. 
2) COVID-verbal: Tweets and other text jokes that usually did not include pictures.  
3) COVID-strip: Comic strip or political cartoons that covered COVID topics. 
4) Non-COVID-verbal: Tweets and other text jokes that did not include pictures.  
 
We additionally ensured that the text included in these images did not include obvious 
offensive material or language.  
